Seeing the latest log dump you&#39;ve uploaded, I think the real problem
is with this exception, indicative of a bug fixed just yesterday:

Exception in thread &quot;ToeThread #26: &quot; java.lang.ArithmeticException: / by zero
		 at org.archive.crawler.frontier.WorkQueueFrontier.averageDepth(WorkQueueFrontier.java:1257)
		 at org.archive.crawler.admin.StatisticsTracker.averageDepth(StatisticsTracker.java:634)
		 at org.archive.crawler.admin.StatisticsTracker.logActivity(StatisticsTracker.java:231)
		 at org.archive.crawler.framework.AbstractTracker.crawlEnded(AbstractTracker.java:313)
		 at org.archive.crawler.admin.StatisticsTracker.crawlEnded(StatisticsTracker.java:781)
		 at org.archive.crawler.framework.CrawlController.sendCrawlStateChangeEvent(CrawlController.java:966)
		 at org.archive.crawler.framework.CrawlController.completeStop(CrawlController.java:1033)
		 at org.archive.crawler.framework.CrawlController.toeEnded(CrawlController.java:1834)
		 at org.archive.crawler.framework.ToeThread.run(ToeThread.java:190)

This thread is dying of the exception early in AbstractTracker.crawlEnded(),
before dumpReports() is run.

The relevant bug report is:

   [ 1370761 ] ArithmeticException: / by 0 WorkQueueFrontier.averageDepth
   https://sourceforge.net/tracker/?func=detail&atid=539099&aid=1370761&group_id=73833

Give the latest code a try, see if this problem still occurs.

- Gordon @ IA


Gordon Mohr wrote:
&gt; After looking at your HeritrixLauncher class, I suspect the
&gt; problem is a thread deadlock.
&gt; 
&gt; requestCrawlStop() is only called inside doCrawlLoop, which
&gt; holds the synchronization monitor on the HeritrixLauncher
&gt; instance. However, one of the effects of requestCrawlStop()
&gt; is to inform all listeners that the crawl is ending -- and
&gt; this will usually happen from the ToeThread that notices
&gt; the crawl is truly ending, not the thread that initiated
&gt; the requestCrawlStop().
&gt; 
&gt; However, your SimpleCrawlStatusListener.crawlEnded() method
&gt; to receive this notification also seeks to obtain a lock
&gt; on the HeritrixLauncher instance -- resulting in a deadlock.
&gt; 
&gt; If this is the problem, it should be obvious in the SIGQUIT
&gt; thread dump -- that dump will itself run a simple deadlock
&gt; detection algorithm and show the results at the bottom of
&gt; the dump.
&gt; 
&gt; - Gordon @ IA
